comment: Larkin (NYK) comes over Wiggins' (MIN) back and makes contact with him in a manner that prevents him from securing the rebound.
Martin (MIN) switches his pivot foot on the step-back jump shot attempt.
Wiggins (MIN) hooks Acy (NYK) as he spins into the lane.
Dieng (MIN) does not establish legal guarding position and is still sliding to his left when he makes contact with Larkin (NYK).
Dieng (MIN) makes contact with Shved's (NYK) arm and body and the contact affects his movement to the basket.
Thomas (NYK) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Martin (MIN) on the perimeter.
Dieng (MIN) cleanly knocks the ball away from Aldrich (NYK).
Shved (NYK) and Wiggins (MIN) clamp one another, but separate immediately.
Shved (NYK) makes contact with Wiggins' (MIN) body and the contact affects his shot attempt.
Dieng (MIN) sets the screen on Galloway (NYK) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
LaVine (MIN) puts two hands on the ball during his crossover move on the drive to the basket.
Wiggins (MIN) cleanly blocks the jump shot attempt by Shved (NYK).
Shved (NYK) and Wiggins (MIN) lock and clamp each other while establishing position but the rebound is out of their reach.
Shved (NYK) makes contact with Wiggins' (MIN) arm and the contact affects his movement to the basket.
Martin (MIN) avoids making contact with Bargnani (NYK) in a manner that affects his movement to the basket.
Shved (NYK) brings his arms down and makes contact with Wiggins (MIN), affecting his movement to the basket.
Bargnani (NYK) does not make contact with Wiggins (MIN) and affect his movement to the basket.
Dieng (MIN) comes into contact with Galloway (NYK) as he cuts away from the ball but the contact does not affect his FOM.
Budinger (MIN) moves into Shved's (NYK) body on the shot attempt and the contact affects his movement to the basket.
Dieng (MIN) blocks the ball before it reaches its apex.
Galloway (NYK) grabs LaVine (MIN) to prevent him from attempting the layup.
Shved (MIN) loses his balance and there is no contact that affects his drive down the lane.
Galloway (NYK) commits a take foul from behind on LaVine (MIN), but the foul should have been ruled a clear path foul.
